    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team reviewed available simulation and experimental evidence for the VAD hemolysis prediction model. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification results indicate hemolysis predictions remain below the absolute clinical threshold across all five operating points with acceptable confidence bounds. The overall body of evidence is considered sufficient to support regulatory submission. Several factors were not fully characterized; however, the team judged the residual gaps to be manageable given the conservative uncertainty margins demonstrated in the UQ analysis.",
